# See docs: https://docs.docker.com/build/concepts/context/#dockerignore-files
# The Docker Compose' build-context is "the repository root", because we want to access the shared "packages" folder inside each service.
# So we exclude files and directories that are not needed for building the image, to speed up the build process.
# The Dockerfiles primarily need content from `packages/` and `services/`, so we ignore several known-unneeded paths instead of using a strict allowlist.

.git
.env*
.dockerignore
Dockerfile

# Directories not needed for Docker builds
interfaces/
e2e/
k6/
tools/
docs/
downloads/
resources/

# Dependencies
node_modules

# Generated files
coverage
dist
www
.angular
.nyc_output
.swc

# Logs
logs
*.log

# IDE / OS
.vscode
.DS_Store

# Root-level config files not needed inside containers
*.md
*.mjs
lint-staged.config.mjs
